time/sktime/issues/3885","id":1338096859,"node_id":"IC_kwDOCVKAsc5Pwbzb","user":{"login":"ltsaprounis","id":64217214,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY0MjE3MjE0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/64217214?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis","html_url":"https://github.com/ltsaprounis","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-12-05T20:06:03Z","updated_at":"2022-12-05T20:06:03Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Nice catch @bryancarlo! \r\n\r\nI wasn't sure what the right behaviour for the Croston in-sample predictions is, so after some quick googling I landed on a [Stephan Kolassa Cross-Validated answer](https://stats.stackexchange.com/questions/127337/explain-the-croston-method-of-r) (as usual 😄) that gives an example with in-sample predictions:\r\n\r\nIn sktime the predicted value is the constant for the forecasted value, which is correct for forecasting but wrong for in-sample predictions. https://github.com/sktime/sktime/blob/18b502e969d9c8d8dafce5cea78eb0c43fe23d91/sktime/forecasting/croston.py#L152\r\n\r\nI think the R implementation of croston in the tsintermitent package is able to supply in-sample forecasts. \r\nRelevant code here:\r\nhttps://github.com/trnnick/tsintermittent/blob/ac26f9c516f06ab1fcb9a1a494f8b2b1f86aa0b1/R/crost.R#L167\r\n\r\nWhen I get some time I can add this in our implementation as well, **or** if you're feeling brave you can fix it yourself with a Pull Request (see the developer guide here -> https://www.sktime.org/en/stable/developer_guide.html)","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/comments/1338096859/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"ltsaprounis","id":64217214,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY0MjE3MjE0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/64217214?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis","html_url":"https://github.com/ltsaprounis","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ltsaprounis/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}},{"id":7958569004,"node_id":"MEE_lADOCVKAsc5X9ON7zwAAAAHaXiAs","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/events/7958569004","actor":{"login":"bryancarlo","id":60631662,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYwNjMxNjYy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/60631662?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bryancarlo","html_url":"https://github.com/bryancarlo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bryancarlo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bryancarlo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github